abstract: WASHINGTON, Dec. 12--The Senate passed and sent to President Carter today a three-year extension of the revenue-sharing program for distributing Federal money to cities and states.

abstract: Al Davis, chief executive officer of the Oakland Raiders, has charged that Georgia Frontiere, the owner of the Los Angeles Rams, sold tickets to last season's Super Bowl game at above their face value, and that Pete Rozelle, the comissioner of the National Football League, may also have profited from such sales.

abstract: HASTINGS-ON-HUDSON THE most striking thing, per  haps, was the fullness of the sound. The evening, after all, had been described as a hoote  nanny and a formal gathering of those who play folk music, and the connotation was of two or three guitars and just as many soft and silvery voices.

THE legend and the life of Woody Guthrie are intertwined by journalist Joe Klein into a su  perbly balanced biography of the folk hero and folk singer. In Guthrie Mr. Klein defines an essential character in the American dream. Whether the boy (he is always a boy, or a boy-man) is fictional, or has lived, doesn't matter.
headline_main: This Land Was His Land; Guthrie
